1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,319
previously on Dumbgeons and Dragons.

2
00:00:02,319 --> 00:00:06,960
Do you know how Aurel escaped the fate of the other gods?

3
00:00:06,960 --> 00:00:11,519
Maybe the Brotherhood has more information. Most of us just are thankful,

4
00:00:11,519 --> 00:00:17,920
but her power seems to be waning as well. She looks up and says, oh, Thea and friends.

5
00:00:18,480 --> 00:00:20,879
Macath, some things don't change.

6
00:00:20,879 --> 00:00:29,600
I seek the gods. I seek my god, who I thought abandoned us.

7
00:00:29,679 --> 00:00:38,079
If you find the gods, they will be able to help undo what Orcus has done.

8
00:00:39,359 --> 00:00:45,600
But you have no further insight from all your hundreds of mages.

9
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:46,719
We know where they are not.

10
00:00:46,719 --> 00:00:48,079
It is more than I had before.

11
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:55,040
We need to decide what we will do, how we survive without using magic.

12
00:00:55,040 --> 00:00:56,880
Use it when it matters.

13
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:59,359
How long is it going to take us to find the gods?

14
00:00:59,519 --> 00:01:05,039
But how do we say that getting back to Flint to do a ritual that might not even work

15
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,000
is worth the whole world?

16
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,319
I think we also seek the gods.

17
00:01:11,439 --> 00:01:14,640
Good. Four swords better than one.

18
00:01:17,519 --> 00:01:20,719
Welcome to Dumbgeons and Dragons. I'm your dungeon master, Russ More.

19
00:01:20,719 --> 00:01:23,439
He, him also with me today is Amy More.

20
00:01:24,079 --> 00:01:28,960
Yes, she, her, and I am playing Thea Amastasia. Also, she, her.

21
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:29,920
And Tom Laird.

22
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:35,040
Yeah, that's me, he, him, and I am playing Tulgier, who also goes by he, him.

23
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:36,320
And Carla Maxted.

24
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:41,360
She, her, playing Yenbul Nury, who also goes by she, her.

25
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:44,160
And joining us again this week, because we just can't get enough,

26
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:46,640
it's Kristin Flemmons from the Broad Swords.

27
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,840
Can't get rid of me.

28
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:49,680
Hi.

29
00:01:49,680 --> 00:01:50,640
We did not try to.

30
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:54,000
Tricked you into coming back against your will.

31
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,360
You think it's your idea.

32
00:01:56,159 --> 00:02:00,400
You know, that's a, that's a mind twist that I'm okay with.

33
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:04,560
But yes, I will once again be playing Agath, god-lost,

34
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,560
Cathlo Olavi.

35
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:10,479
I think I screwed up my own name, but both she and I go by she, her.

36
00:02:10,479 --> 00:02:11,520
Goliaths are tough.

37
00:02:13,520 --> 00:02:17,039
Sometimes it gets smooth and then other times it's like, just call me,

38
00:02:17,039 --> 00:02:17,759
just call me A.

39
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:23,920
Just go with Lady A, that name's never been used before.

40
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:25,680
Never, not once.

41
00:02:25,680 --> 00:02:26,800
No, no, it's all good.

42
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:30,000
Where we have another Goliath is over on Patreon.

43
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,840
Amy plays that Goliath in another game.

44
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:36,560
And I mean, secondary character to some of the other characters.

45
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,480
But we'll come over.

46
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:42,720
Wow, that's how we're starting this.

47
00:02:42,720 --> 00:02:45,520
So that's the kind of energy Russ brings when he's a player,

48
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:50,000
if you'd like to hear that game where Tom is a very kind and nice DM.

49
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:53,280
That's right.

50
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,599
Patreon.com slash dumb dragon cast, where when you are a patron,

51
00:02:55,599 --> 00:02:56,879
you get an episode dedicated to you.

52
00:02:56,879 --> 00:03:00,719
Like today's patron, Deej Deman.

53
00:03:00,719 --> 00:03:01,759
Deej Deman.

54
00:03:01,759 --> 00:03:02,319
Deej.

55
00:03:02,319 --> 00:03:02,879
That's right.

56
00:03:02,879 --> 00:03:03,599
Thanks, Deej.

57
00:03:03,599 --> 00:03:04,159
Awesome.

58
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:05,840
I feel like I'm on an episode of Full House.

59
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:06,560
Thanks, Deej.

60
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:08,879
Amazing.

61
00:03:08,879 --> 00:03:09,360
Yep.

62
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,599
Patreon.com slash dumb dragon cast.

63
00:03:11,599 --> 00:03:12,960
And now, fuck it, let's play.

64
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:25,520
Your group has been in Bryn Shander for three days now,

65
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:27,840
poring over the notebooks of the Arkane Brotherhood.

66
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:31,840
You spent time with Macoth, tracing over the previous explorers'

67
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:36,640
maps and writings, trying to piece together where the gods have been hidden or locked away.

68
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,520
We hear Macoth speak.

69
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,640
Luskin was a stronghold.

70
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,400
Much like Waterdeep was.

71
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:50,400
Orcus's forces, for a long time, could not break the barriers set up by the Brotherhood.

72
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:54,480
We created a barrier, much like the one that looms

73
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:58,000
low now over the top of what remains of Icewind Dale.

74
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:05,520
This was before we truly knew the gods were gone and that our efforts were for nothing.

75
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:12,000
In the coming months, the barrier we were able to maintain got smaller and smaller.

76
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,840
We couldn't explain why.

77
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,599
Nothing had changed.

78
00:04:15,599 --> 00:04:19,759
The spells were the same, our focus had waned marginally,

79
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:22,800
but we had enough wizards to create a rotation.

80
00:04:23,759 --> 00:04:26,079
We thought it had to be an external force,

81
00:04:26,079 --> 00:04:30,639
something that Orcus and his followers were employing beyond our walls.

82
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:34,480
Then death began creeping in.

83
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:40,720
Seemingly beneath the barrier, trees and animals on our side began to die.

84
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:46,080
Then people, healthy people, began to drop for no reason.

85
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:53,040
One day they were helping the cause, the next they would cease to be living.

86
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:57,120
Until they started to rise again.

87
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:05,600
You don't know the fear until you're staring down a hideous enemy with an endless supply

88
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:11,920
of creatures only to have your own turn into that which you are fighting on your own side

89
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,560
of the wall.

90
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,200
We didn't know what to do.

91
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:18,640
We locked up in the tower with as many people as we could and blew the bridge.

92
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,240
We lost so many.

93
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:24,720
We could have saved more if only there was more time.

94
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:26,879
We were shaken and lost focus.

95
00:05:26,879 --> 00:05:29,040
The walls came down and we were overrun.

96
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:34,720
We narrowed our focus to protect the tower and now that it was closer,

97
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:36,320
we could see the damage beyond.

98
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:40,720
The fields of death, the forests gone, the rivers and ocean blackened.

99
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:44,080
Orcus was winning and we were the ones helping him.

100
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,720
We couldn't explain it.

101
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:50,240
Magic draws from the land and the land is replenished by the gods.

102
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:55,280
But when the gods were called, there was no answer.

103
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,600
Did they leave us?

104
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,240
Move on to another world that was in better shape?

105
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,920
That was filled with more hope?

106
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:04,480
Or were they trapped?

107
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:09,040
We heard of a refuge here in Icewind Dale.

108
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,360
A god remained.

109
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,520
Aurel remained.

110
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:16,240
Her own paranoia saved her.

111
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:20,320
She was shielded by the blizzards of Icewind Dale and Orcus's followers

112
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:23,840
couldn't find any towns let alone a god hidden within the storms.

113
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,560
We came any way we could.

114
00:06:27,440 --> 00:06:32,320
Many were lost in the trek across Faerun and as we still are,

115
00:06:32,319 --> 00:06:35,839
we were scared to teleport or use any magic

116
00:06:35,839 --> 00:06:37,920
for fear of furthering Orcus's plans.

117
00:06:38,639 --> 00:06:41,279
It took months of travel to finally make it.

118
00:06:42,639 --> 00:06:47,600
We were less than half the number we were when we started but thankful to arrive.

119
00:06:48,319 --> 00:06:51,920
The blizzards parted and led us here to Bryn Shander.

120
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,759
We've been here ever since.

121
00:06:55,839 --> 00:06:59,600
Orl could sense the gods had left the world

122
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,840
but that they were still within reach.

123
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:04,640
Not abandoned but imprisoned.

124
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:08,560
Shrouded in a cloud of evil and death that she could not break through.

125
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:12,560
Orl's powers are fading as well.

126
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:16,960
The last known god fueling the entire world.

127
00:07:17,760 --> 00:07:22,080
The blizzard stopped and she diverted her energy to the barrier you came through

128
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:23,840
which gets smaller every day.

129
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:28,560
We began sending out scouts and wizards and explorers

130
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:33,120
to try and find any sign of the gods or the place they could be kept.

131
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:35,199
And so far nothing has turned up.

132
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:39,680
We are down to only a few of our original number.

133
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:43,439
Traveling through the plains of course is a dangerous task

134
00:07:43,439 --> 00:07:48,560
and what we found is that it is as unforgiving as it is here within the material plane

135
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:52,319
as Orcus's reach extends throughout all known realms

136
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:55,439
and the more life that is lost the more power he gains.

137
00:07:55,439 --> 00:08:00,719
We've received reports back from all the planes except these four.

138
00:08:00,719 --> 00:08:06,079
Avernus, Pandemonium, Carceri, and Limbo.

139
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:10,879
But everywhere we've been the rulers have changed.

140
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:15,920
Demon lords have been given control of the planes

141
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:20,079
and present even more chaos than what could already be expected.

142
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:27,279
Well, I'm so sorry for everyone you've lost.

143
00:08:33,039 --> 00:08:42,480
I have to say it's a little demoralizing hearing of this,

144
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:52,000
but I mean we're here to help in any way we can.

145
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,720
So tell us about Limbo.

146
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:03,440
It sounds like the four worst places.

147
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:06,000
So Pandemonium, that can't be good.

148
00:09:07,039 --> 00:09:08,159
Limbo, I mean-

149
00:09:08,159 --> 00:09:09,920
There's just a lot going on in Pandemonium.

150
00:09:09,919 --> 00:09:13,919
Yeah. What was the other? Avernus?

151
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:16,000
Avernus and Carceri.

152
00:09:16,959 --> 00:09:21,120
Limbo is a plane of pure chaos.

153
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:26,240
You could call it a roiling soup of impermanent matter and energy.

154
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:30,240
Neat. How on earth does one find a god in a place like that?

155
00:09:30,799 --> 00:09:32,639
This has been the problem.

156
00:09:32,639 --> 00:09:37,120
Right. Have you tried tying a rope onto someone and then sending them in?

157
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:41,279
Travel between all of these places happens through the astral plane.

158
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:47,919
I was just trying to lighten the mood. It's not a serious suggestion.

159
00:09:50,799 --> 00:09:51,519
Shall I go on?

160
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:55,360
Yes, can you please tell us about the other planes?

161
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:59,120
Well, it doesn't get better if that's what you're hoping for.

162
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:02,480
Pandemonium is a plane of madness,

163
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:08,399
a great mass of rock riddled with tunnels carved by howling winds.

164
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:14,639
It's cold and noisy and dark with no natural light there.

165
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:20,240
Well, that one does sound quite bad.

166
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:26,720
Now, Carceri is a model for all other prisons in existence.

167
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:36,399
It's a plane of desolation and despair and holds layers of vast bogs and fetid jungles

168
00:10:36,399 --> 00:10:42,560
and deserts and jagged mountains surrounded by frigid oceans and black ice.

169
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:46,560
I mean, I feel like that's probably the one we're going to need to go to.

170
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:51,759
Would it be too literal to imprison the gods in a prison plane?

171
00:10:52,559 --> 00:10:54,080
Okay, all right.

172
00:10:54,080 --> 00:11:02,319
Macoth, what has been your experience of Orcus and his humor? Is he always so on the nose?

173
00:11:02,319 --> 00:11:05,039
He hasn't shown a great amount of humor.

174
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:12,080
You know, sometimes the evildoers do tricks.

175
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:20,879
I understand a lighter foe might throw a gaff or a guffaw.

176
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:22,960
A quick pun.

177
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:23,919
A quick yes.

178
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:29,919
But no, just constant unending stream of undead.

179
00:11:29,919 --> 00:11:32,319
Death. Yeah.

180
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,639
Great, great.

181
00:11:34,639 --> 00:11:38,000
And Avernus, one of the harder ones to get to,

182
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,879
as we can't get to it through a planar portal,

183
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:46,799
we'd have to find a way to enter the nine hells.

184
00:11:47,439 --> 00:11:51,279
Which hell is Avernus out of the nine, if you were to rank it from one to nine?

185
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:52,559
Number one.

186
00:11:53,759 --> 00:11:57,439
Okay, wait, number one, like it's the best hell or it's the first hell?

187
00:11:57,439 --> 00:12:01,919
And is best the worst or is worst the best?

188
00:12:01,919 --> 00:12:04,319
Or is it the first one you can get to?

189
00:12:04,319 --> 00:12:05,279
It's very bad.

190
00:12:05,279 --> 00:12:07,200
Is it a layered, like a layered cake?

191
00:12:08,319 --> 00:12:09,039
What layer would it be?

192
00:12:09,039 --> 00:12:10,720
Were we going right to the bottom of the cake?

193
00:12:11,840 --> 00:12:17,840
Okay, how bad would it be if you went to Avernus and you ran into Tiamat?

194
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:19,039
Because Tiamat is there.

195
00:12:19,679 --> 00:12:20,879
Or at least was there.

196
00:12:20,879 --> 00:12:23,039
I don't know if she remains.

197
00:12:23,039 --> 00:12:24,960
I mean, she probably wouldn't be thrilled to see this one.

198
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,639
They have a bit of history, it'd be quite bad.

199
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:33,759
Quite bad.

200
00:12:35,039 --> 00:12:37,519
Awkward could be a description?

201
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,279
Really awkward?

202
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:40,399
I don't know.

203
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,799
Your relationship with her?

204
00:12:42,799 --> 00:12:43,679
I mean, I know you.

205
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:45,279
I mean, they didn't date or anything.

206
00:12:45,279 --> 00:12:45,919
I don't think.

207
00:12:45,919 --> 00:12:48,799
No, she just killed my best friend.

208
00:12:48,799 --> 00:12:49,440
No big deal.

209
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,680
Yes, exactly.

210
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,280
Yeah, yeah, soup's awkward.

211
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:57,360
Okay, well, I don't want to go to Avernus if we could just,

212
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:00,000
like, because I mean, we can't go everywhere, right?

213
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:02,560
So if we could just knock one off the list for now.

214
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:03,600
Leave it till last.

215
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:05,600
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

216
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:08,960
I like your optimism.

217
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:11,040
We will get through three others.

218
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,280
I mean, hey, we could get lucky.

219
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:16,240
First one we go to, we could, you know, get it rich

220
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:18,000
and then not have to go to the other three.

221
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,360
That is an option.

222
00:13:19,360 --> 00:13:20,720
Yeah, that's a possibility.

223
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,759
I hope that's the case for you.

224
00:13:24,639 --> 00:13:28,960
I also don't like the sound of pandemonium.

225
00:13:29,759 --> 00:13:35,360
Dark, unending caves, madness, cold, also noisy.

226
00:13:35,360 --> 00:13:37,440
This sounds very bad.

227
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,200
I don't have dark vision.

228
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:41,279
That sucks.

229
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:46,720
So not my first choice.

230
00:13:47,279 --> 00:13:50,240
Why don't we go for the obvious prison?

231
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:54,320
Yes, perhaps Orcus is evil, but not imaginative.

232
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,680
Perhaps.

233
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,200
So you would like to go to Corsairi?

234
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:58,879
No, we wouldn't like to go to any of these places.

235
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:00,800
I don't really think a like is...

236
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:01,840
That would be stretching it.

237
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:02,720
Yes.

238
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:08,320
Your wish is to start your search in Corsairi.

239
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:14,399
Have you sent anyone else to Corsairis or Corsairin?

240
00:14:14,399 --> 00:14:15,920
I keep saying Corsairi.

241
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:17,920
Corsairi.

242
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:18,560
So neither.

243
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:19,440
No.

244
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:20,399
Okay.

245
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,800
It's mystery option C.

246
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:23,680
You did not list.

247
00:14:24,399 --> 00:14:24,720
Yes.

248
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:27,680
Have you sent others to Corsairi?

249
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:28,560
Yes.

250
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:33,519
Yes, there was a band of wizards we sent and have yet to hear from.

